    <exercise xml:id="STAT-zHuQEGSH8Y" original="STAT/modules/m79632/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>Try It</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Consider the function <em>f</em>(<m>x</m>) = <m>\frac{\text{ 1 }}{8}</m> for 0 ≤ <m>x</m> ≤ 8. Draw the graph of <em>f</em>(<m>x</m>) and find <m>P</m>(2.5 &lt; <m>x</m> &lt; 7.5).</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <figure xml:id="STAT-28me9ziNNf" original="STAT/modules/m79632/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <caption>A graph is shown. The x axis of the graph is labeled “The uniform distribution” and is measured from 0 to 10.A box starts on 2 and extends to around 8.8. The box is shaded blue between the measurements of 3 to 6. Above the blue box, text reads “shaded area represents P (3 &lt; x &lt; 6)”.</caption>
          <image source="STAT/CNX_Stats_C05_M02_tryit001anno.jpg" width="80%" />
        </figure>
        <p>
          <m>P</m> (2.5 &lt; <m>x</m> &lt; 7.5) = 0.625</p>
      </solution>
    </exercise>
  
